Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Workplace 2

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/workplace-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/workplace-6-7)

Workplace 2 features a clean and intuitive user interface (UI) to simplify and declutter customer communication workflows. The entire lifecycle of a Business Case can be completed and monitored from this central application.

Read on to find out more about the UI of Workplace 2.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The UI of Workplace 2 UI consist of three main regions:

- Global **search bar**

- Left side panel with **vertical tabs**:

![](data:image/png;base64,) **Dashboard tab**: Central page allowing quick access to favorited and recently viewed Business Cases

- ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Business Cases tab**: Card overview of all available Business Cases

- ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Business Case Instances tab**: Table overview of all Business Case Instances

- ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Tasks tab**: Table overview of all Human Tasks coming from Business Case Instances

- ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Problems &amp; Events**:** **List of events, warnings, and errors with detailed messages

- Central **work area **which displays the contents of the selected vertical tab

> Tip: Collapsible sidebar

If you need more screen space to comfortably view the table of tasks or Business Case Instances, you can collapse the sidebar by clicking the arrow icon. It appears when hovering the cursor over the dividing line between the sidebar and the right-hand area.

## Dashboard tab
The Dashboard is the start page of Workplace after logging into the portal. It displays favorited and recently opened Business Cases as tiles. Business Cases can be viewed and started from here.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Business Cases tab
Once a Business Case has been configured and uploaded by the Workplace administrator, its displayed as a tile in the Business Cases tab. The tab acts as a collector for all Business Cases which the user is authorized to view. Business Cases can be started from here.

![workplace_tab business cases.png](data:image/png;base64,)

## Business Case Instances tab
Once a Business Case has been started, it becomes a unique Business Case Instance. The Business Case Instances tab provides a fully searchable and sortable table view of Business Case Instances. Individual Business Case Instances can be opened from here, and the management of multiple Business Case Instances is made convenient through bulk actions.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Tasks tab
Human Tasks are the building blocks of a Business Case. They are actionable steps which require some form of user input, for example editing a document template in Composer or sending it through email to an end customer. The Tasks tab lists all tasks in a fully searchable and sortable table, and provides bulk actions for convenient task management.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Task editor
Whenenever a Business Case Instance is started or reopened, its opened at its current step in a separate editor. This editor consists of a sidebar for navigation and a large work interface where all necessary user input can be provided.

![Email composition interface showing fields for recipient, subject, and message body.](data:image/png;base64,)

## Problems &amp; Events tab
Whenever an event, warning or error occurs in Workplace 2, a notification snackbar is displayed in the lower left corner of the screen. Additionally, it is registered in the Problems &amp; Events tab where it can be filtered and searched.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Business Cases are interactive processes which are started and completed from Workplace. A Business Case typically consists of one or several Human Tasks, which require user input in order to advance the process. An open Business Case is called a Business Case Instance.

Composer is a web-based application for editing document templates which were created with Business Designer. It is used mainly to resolve dynamic fields into real data read from a database.
